Market Segmentation: 
Flexible plastic packaging companies is segmented on the basis of type, material, printing technology and application. The growth amongst the different segments helps you in attaining the knowledge related to the different growth factors expected to be prevalent throughout the market and formulate different strategies to help identify core application areas and the difference in your target markets. 
On the basis of type, the flexible plastic packaging market is segmented into stand-up pouches, flat pouches, rollstocks, gusseted bags, wicketed bags, wraps and others. Stand-up pouches is further sub segmented into standard stand-up pouches and retort stand-up pouches. Flat pouches is further sub segmented into standard flat pouches and retort flat pouches.
On the basis of material, the flexible plastic packaging market is segmented into plastic films, paper, aluminum foil, bioplastics. Plastic films is further sub segmented into polypropylene, polyethylene, poly vinyl chloride, biaxiallyoriented polyethylene terephthalate, ethylene vinyl alcohol, polyamide and polystyrene.
On the basis of printing technology, the flexible plastic packaging market is segmented into flexography, rotogravure, digital printing and other printing technologies.
On the basis of application, the flexible plastic packaging market is segmented into food and beverage, healthcare, cosmetics and toiletries, industrial and institutional, tobacco products and other applications.
